5:
...These prices are insane. How can
they afford to sell such a fatty fish at
this price?!
9:
Heh, this place is well-known for its
fish. Great quality and a whole lot of
them, too! We should come back
and do some shopping next time.
13:
This place is lovely.
Looks really peaceful, but...
17:
The pirates here like to stay off the
radar.
19:
They go into hiding the second they
see the Blaue Fraxis. That's why
we've got to keep a low profile...
24:
Catch the thieves red-handed and
teach 'em a lesson? Sounds like a
fun time to me.
28:
Haha. I knew it was a good idea
bringing you all along as backup!
31:
Now then, let's get to work.
Things are about to get real busy.
36:
...I guess that's everything for
today.
Hmph. Can't believe they've been
hoarding all this to themselves.
41:
Yeah, yeah. You don't got nothing to
worry ab—
44: Hm? What's this about a promise?
48:
Surprise, surprise. No trade licenses
to be found here! Looks like this
whole operation is totally illegal!
52:
Shoddy job, guys. If you're going to
commit a crime, you've gotta be a
little quicker!
56:
Great work, you two! Can't ask for
better efficiency than that!
60:
...I get the feeling you didn't need our
help.
64:
You're the ringleader, right? Have
anything to say for yourself?
67:
...Tch! I ain't got nothing to say to
some government dog, and you're
not gonna be around long enough
for it to matter, anyway!
69:
O-only the poor can understand our
suffering. You wealthy folk only care
about yourselves!
71: ...Rob or be robbed. Is that it?
74:
I'm hearing nothing but excuses,
and none of them justify your theft!
77:
An empty speech from a rich brat!
There's no hope for the rest of us!
84:
And there always will be as long as
we never give up!
87:
We all have a future, and we all
have hope!
94:
You're all from a Float that's fallen
on hard times, huh.
97:
You sent everything you stole back
home, didn't you?
103:
No matter how bleak things seem,
you've never given up.
106:
The rage in your hearts and fight in
your souls wouldn't let you.
110: Do we really have to take them in?
117:
It is. But... I don't know if just throwing
them in jail is going to really fix
anything.
120:
...You don't intend on ending things
here, do you?
124:
Heh-heh, it's an honor to be thought
so highly of!
127:
I've spoken to a mediator. Starting
next week, resource shipments will
be sent to your Float.
130:
Only temporarily, mind you. At the
very least, everyone back home
shouldn't have to worry about food
for a while.
133:
...I'm sorry I couldn't help you all
sooner.
137:
However, I still have high hopes for
all of you. Once you've atoned for
your wrongdoing, I hope you'll visit
the Blaue Fraxis if you're ever feeling
stuck.
140:
We can't give up on one another, so
let's do everything we can do build a
brighter future for everyone!
151:
W-welcome back. It really... dragged
out this time, huh?
155:
Turns out they weren't too happy
about me talking to a mediator.
Hard to get a win in this world, huh?
160: Are things gonna be all right?
164:
Well, you know. The folks on top
aren't so big on helping the little guy.
166:
They told me that once a Float
becomes too difficult to maintain,
we can decide to either have it
scrapped or merged with another
Float.
174:
Heh! Glad I'm not the only one who
feels that way.
177:
Do you two think our future will wind
up the way we're hoping for?
182:
Come on, you already know the
answer.
186:
Who knows if things will turn out
exactly how we want, but I know
things will change.
188:
After all, there's plenty of people like
Fraxis on these seas, right?
204:
Geez, you've gotta cool it with the
smacking.
209:
Now then, time to get back to work!
I've gotta draw up some application
forms, fill out those trade
documents...
213:
Gonna do this the boring way, huh?
You do you, I guess.
217:
Don't you worry now. As soon as 
I start feeling a little worn-out, 
you'll be seeing me for dinner!
222:
We'll be looking forward to the
souvenirs you bring, then.
227:
Haha, you got it! I'm looking forward
to it, you guys!
231:
I finally got my hands on a bottle of
the good stuff.
234: You'll be joining me, won't you, Fraxis?
238: I see you haven't changed a bit...
242:
...Heh! You bet! Let's live it up until we
see the sun!
